Description: Neck and shoulder sherd (mended from three fragments) of East Greek black-glazed pottery trefoil--mouthed oinochoe; interior: glazed save for reserved band (with some dilute glaze) on shoulder; exterior glazed; inscription on exterior.
Bibliographic references: Petrie 1886 / Naukratis. Part I., 1884-85 (pl. XXXIII, no. 229)
Bernand 1970 / Le Delta égyptien d'après les textes grecs, i: les confins libyques (p. 662, no. 190)
Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GO.584)
